<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="303" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,430]" box="[199,943,150,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species belongs to 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[590,599,150,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">‘</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[599,854,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Agauopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipalpus">
<emphasis box="[599,854,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Agauopsis brevipalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group’.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
<bibRefCitation author="Rao, G. C. &amp; Ganapati, G." box="[199,470,187,214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="82 - 125" refId="ref13546" refString="Rao, G. C. &amp; Ganapati, G. (1968) The interstitial fauna inhabiting the beach sands of Waltair coast. Proceedings of the National Institute of Sciences of India, B, 34, 82 - 125." type="journal article" year="1968">Rao &amp; Ganapati (1968)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName authority="Trouessart" authorityName="Trouessart" box="[582,965,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Agauopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipalpus">
<emphasis box="[582,839,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Agauopsis brevipalpus</emphasis>
Trouessart
</taxonomicName>
in the fauna from interstitial sand of Visakhapatnam (= Waltair) coast, 
<collectingRegion box="[513,695,223,249]" country="India" name="Andhra Pradesh" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Andhra Pradesh</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingRegion box="[712,759,223,249]" country="Cayman Islands" name="West Bay" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Bay</collectingRegion>
of Bengal). 
<bibRefCitation author="Chatterjee, T." box="[906,1110,222,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="431 - 434" refId="ref9977" refString="Chatterjee, T. (1995 a) Occurence of Agauopsis brevipalpus Trouessart (Halacaridae: Acari) from west coast of India. Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, 92, 431 - 434." type="journal article" year="1995">Chatterjee (1995a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chatterjee, T." box="[1124,1194,223,250]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="141 - 143" refId="ref10100" refString="Chatterjee, T. (1996 a) Record of Copidognathus temaeus Bartsch (Halacaridae: Acari) from Indian Ocean. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of India, 38 (1 &amp; 2), 141 - 143." type="journal article" year="1996">1996a</bibRefCitation>
) documented 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Agauopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipalpus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">A. brevipalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Kovalam beach, 
<collectingRegion box="[507,582,259,285]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Kerala</collectingRegion>
(Arabian Sea). After more careful examinations of individuals from 
<collectingRegion box="[1362,1437,259,285]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Kerala</collectingRegion>
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, I. &amp; Chatterjee, T." box="[151,473,295,321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="321 - 327" refId="ref9771" refString="Bartsch, I. &amp; Chatterjee, T. (2001) A new species of the Agauopsis brevipalpus - group from India (Acari: Halacaridae). Entomologische Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg, 13, 321 - 327." type="journal article" year="2001">Bartsch &amp; Chatterjee (2001)</bibRefCitation>
considered that these to be similar but not conspecific with 
<taxonomicName box="[1159,1322,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Agauopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipalpus">
<emphasis box="[1159,1322,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">A. brevipalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and consequently described a new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartsch &amp; Chatterjee" authorityYear="2001" box="[552,659,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Agauopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arabia">
<emphasis box="[552,659,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">A. arabia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Collection was made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chatterjee, T. &amp; Annapurna, C. &amp; De Troch, M." box="[954,1229,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="37 - 38" refId="ref11680" refString="Chatterjee, T., Annapurna, C. &amp; De Troch, M. (2004 a) Range extension of Agauopsis arabia Bartsch and Chatterjee (Halacaridae: Acari) along the Indian coast. Journal of Aquatic Biology, 192, 37 - 38." type="journal article" year="2004">
Chatterjee 
<emphasis box="[1077,1127,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">et al</emphasis>
. (2004a)
</bibRefCitation>
from Palm beach, Visakhapatnam, 
<collectingRegion box="[336,516,367,393]" country="India" name="Andhra Pradesh" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Andhra Pradesh</collectingRegion>
indicate that the species from there is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartsch &amp; Chatterjee" authorityYear="2001" box="[946,1052,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Agauopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arabia">
<emphasis box="[946,1052,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">A. arabia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not 
<taxonomicName box="[1148,1310,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Agauopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipalpus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1310,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">A. brevipalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as claimed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rao, G. C. &amp; Ganapati, G." box="[186,454,403,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="82 - 125" refId="ref13546" refString="Rao, G. C. &amp; Ganapati, G. (1968) The interstitial fauna inhabiting the beach sands of Waltair coast. Proceedings of the National Institute of Sciences of India, B, 34, 82 - 125." type="journal article" year="1968">Rao &amp; Ganapati (1968)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
